<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1400,1857]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
<bibRef pageId="3" pageNumber="596" refId="ref1599" type="book">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1688,1713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
<title box="[199,268,1688,1713]" jopScore="0.16732542" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">Notes</title>
.
</emphasis>
<journalOrPublisher jopScore="0.35756278" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
The new species is similar to 
<emphasis box="[618,810,1688,1713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">Trifida melichari</emphasis>
(Distant, 1908) in color pattern and male genitalia, but can be distinguished from the later by the aedeagus with the protrusions on the aedeagal shaft more distal and fewer in number, and by the narrower apical part of the dorsal apodeme
</journalOrPublisher>
.
</bibRef>
</paragraph>
