<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="596" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1400,1857]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1797,1822]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[930,1045,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">elegantem</emphasis>
” which means “elegant”, referring to the apical part of the dorsal apodeme of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
